The idea with this app is to make it convenient to collect new information and also make it accessible to activate the knowledge.

All information belongs in a tree.

New nodes "leaves" can be added at any point to this tree.

Any node can be viewed as a markdown like view (i.e. headers and contents and optionally bullet point lists).

Any node can be selected to be part of a flash card system. This flash card system should be able to remember previous interactions
in a way similar to anki flashcards. Allowing saying "easy" bumping the card further into the future, or "forgot" to restart it etc.

Cards should neatly display whether they are flashcards.

The overall layout and drag and drop system should follow the one used in mind, but focusing on this idea in particular. I.e. no projects,
project stacking etc. Only one view where nodes / leaves can be added.

It needs to be easy to rearrange leaves across abstraction levels, i.e. by allowing expanding the sub tree and then drag and drop across.
